question.title: EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION when use Jacoco for tomcat (and seem with hibernate)

node.contents: When I start tomcat with jacoco agent, I get EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION, and tomcat crashed. I noticed that this happen when I include persistent classes which are using by Hibernate. Any one have idea?

astNode.text: When I start tomcat with jacoco agent, I get EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION, and tomcat crashed. I noticed that this happen when I include persistent classes which are using by Hibernate. Any one have idea?
